caption: Great place on the Amsterdam Avenue. Good food, but little bit on the costlier side. The service was nice and friendly.
Awesome service. Fantastic food at great prices and insane portions (for NYC 😂).
Staff was so kind and the food was delicious
When i got my food i had hair in it. More than likely not coming back.
For the first timer's the experience is a bit strange.   When it first opens you go to the bar, order a drink, and wait for table.   However you need to pay your bar tab before going to the table.
Outstanding. So much love! It’s one of the best places I got a delivery from. Meat meals are absolute must.
Food was good I had a good time. Happy New year

Food is yummy and fresh, and it’s pretty true to Greek cuisine. There are also some healthy options. The food is a little pricey (but reasonable in NYC) and the wait was a little long, but it’s wonderful for a nice sit-down dinner.

Great place, nice and friendly service. The food comes with good quality, fresh and with nice portions. The prices are reasonable for manhattan and with good value for money. The dishes are not super creative but simple and tasty. Definitely recommended for a weekday night out. We enjoyed it

I've -embarrassingly- been here more times than I can count and it totally isn't my fault as the meals here are incredibly fresh and oh so satisfying.  Update: I have never been to a restaurant in New York more than 10 times and had only positive things to say but I'm here right now and I can't get over how welcoming everyone is here. You'll always feel like you're at home here, even when you're by yourself.  Giannis deserves a thousand stars. Sorry if I misspelled your name haha
I loved it. Very attentive, friendly and patient. I recommend and will go again.

Ordered a Sam Addams and a Falafel Souvlaki. Was brought a Stella Artois and a pork souvlaki. Pointed at both on the menu, plus I’m a long-time vegetarian. Bad mistake, but a mistake. I’ve gone here before and had better food and service, but I likely won’t return unfortunately.

(Translated by Google) From the area it will be one of the best if you are looking for something medium level, I did not like the baklava. It is walnut and no pistachio.  (Original) De la zona será de los mejores si buscas algo de nivel medio, no me gustó el baklava. Es de nuez y nada de pistache.
Delicious cuisine, charming ambiance!!!

I sent my friends to this place with my highest recommendations. I go their often. This recommendation is always successful. The the food there is great and the crew is welcoming and cooperative. Every time  we go to this place we enjoy a gorgeous time.  highly recommended.
Great atmosphere and delicious food. Big fan of Greek food and this is probably the best one in the area.

Horrible service, took more than 10 minutes for a server to arrive when there was only one other table seated. Low quality ingredients at exorbitant prices. Much better options a couple streets uptown.
I was in the city with my daughter to catch a NCAA Basketball Game at Columbia University,  came across this place. Food, atmosphere, staff 5+☆
Friendly service. Good food.
I came here to have a drink with friends, and the atmosphere was warm and convivial. The staff were all lovely.
Great service and foods.  Will come again.

It’s my first time ordering from this restaurant. I ordered the chicken souvlaki with fries on the side. They even added a free desert. The food was the right temperature and it all tasted delicious. I will definitely be ordering again from them. Also thanks to the manager for the delivery.
Excellent food and very happy environment
(Translated by Google) Good Greek food.  (Original) Buena comida Griega.
Roti chicken is amazing!! Service is quick and friendly...will come back.
Nice place, but takes seriously ages for food to come, and the veggie moussaka turned out to have meat. Would not recommend.

They taut a special outside that they then make a big scene about giving you when the bill comes in 10 dollars more expensive. Then when they do give it to you, they charge you for the fries that came complementary with the meal. None of this explained beforehand. Cherry on top, they refilled our water, and then charged us 3 dollars for the refill. TAP WATER. Said nothing about charging before refilling it. Absolute racket. There are plenty of far superior dining options around here for similar or better cost, namely bar 314, flat top, or even Friedman’s. Will not be returning. Poor business practice.
A cozy Greek restaurant with generous plates and a big bar.
Great Greek food. Tons of seating. I had some good Greek white wine.
Great service. Not a good eggs Benedict. Avoid this menu item. Great dessert.

Mix up when we first got there (me, my wife, friend and his girlfriend). They took a while to get our drinks after we were seated. After that everything was all good. They may have been short handed. A place I would definitely go back to. Food was delicious.
Nice place uptown by Columbia University

Not bad at all. They have a lunch special for less than $10, which is a sandwich and coffee. I think they should just offer a sandwich and a small beverage. Not everybody drinks coffee with a sandwich.
Food was delish and reasonably priced. Service, staff and atmosphere ... definitely an A+++
Had a great time, great food great service.... definitely going back....
Great food and drinks

Came here for lunch with coworkers. Service was very good, and the food was delicious. I had a falafel gyro with fries. I expected the falafel to be dry but it was the complete opposite. You won't notice it from outside on the street but it was very cozy and intimate inside on the day we visited.
Cute, ambient restaurant in the quiet part of the neighborhood. The staff is friendly and helpful!
Great food, nice atmosphere...
Great happy hour menu. Staff were very friendly and attentive.
Good Mediterranean food. Been here a couple of times. Service is a bit slow.

Excellent food and great service. Had branzino for dinner and it was so nice and juicy. Had the opportunity to try some lamb chops and moussaka also cause my friends ordered those and both were incredible also. Definitely have to figure out a time to return there for another round, cause the menu is very nice with so many different variables.

The interiors are amazing and the wait staff were polite and accommodating. However, the food was disappointing. Cauliflower Fritto (deep fried cauliflower) - the opposite of what you expect from a Greek restaurant and healthy Mediterranean cuisine. Moussaka was hot outside and cold inside. It probably means that they reheated in a microwave and they didn’t do a good job. I had few bites and couldn’t finish it. The waiter told me that he can reheated again or even bring different moussaka, but I didn’t think that it will help. There were hardly 5-6 people in restaurant so you can’t say that the kitchen was swamped with orders.
Well prepared comfortable Greek food. Worth visiting if you’re on the area.
Decent tasting food with limited choices.

(Translated by Google) A hidden Greek restaurant. The service staff was very nice, open-minded and fast. The food was very tasty and nicely presented. They offer Greek wines and even Greek beer. But ... quality is correspondingly expensive.  (Original) Ein verstecktes griechisches Lokal. Das Service Personal war sehr nett, aufgeschlossen und schnell.  Das Essen waren sehr schmackhaft  und schön präsentiert.  Sie bieten griechische Weine und sogar griechisches Bier. Aber...Qualität ist entsprechend teuer.
Killer chicken souvlaki and amazing french fries.  Great atmosphere and wonderful service!
Great decor and ambiance, excellent food. It's a good new addition to the restaurant choices on Amsterdam around the Columbia campus.
Had such a great first experience here!! They went above and beyond with drink suggestions and delicious food. Amazing lava cake for a birthday dessert.
Terrible service combinations with so-so food. Last time I was there (three weeks ago) it was so much better so I'll give them another chance.

Food was good the previous times I’ve been here but this time was pretty bad . I ended up waiting almost an hour for a falafel wrap and then when I finally told them I want to take it to go, they then gave me my wrap heated up. Thus , I had heated up yogurt. This restaurant is a hit or miss .
Beautiful, bright brunch spot. Menu is great but be sure to order the souvlaki plate. Side of feta fries was huge. Everything tasted super fresh & amazing! Servers are extremely friendly
Food is OK but not worth the price. Service is too slow.
Cool atmosphere - relaxed but classy with a courteous and quick staff. Can't comment about the food though, since we only went to have a few glasses of champagne.
(Translated by Google) Greek Restaurant with good product and good elaboration  (Original) Restaurant Grec amb bon producte i bona elaboració
Best Mediterranean food on UWS by miles.
Great restaurant and athmoshere
I had dinner with my niece lsdt week ! The place is Amazing and the food is delicious ! Are waiters Sotira so helpful with the menu and her recommendations ! We definitely recommend this place !!!
Great Greek food and ambience. Must visit if you are in the area
Appetizers were fine, food was ok, but every dish came over a huge pile of French fries a top a bed of pita bread. Too much carbs for my taste.

Great atmosphere and feel with great (but could be better) food. The souvlaki platter could have used some more sauce and the meat could have been seasoned better. The octopus appetizer was the highlight. Tender and delicious with accompanying greens. (Are it before I could take a picture). A bit on the pricier side and the wait staff could have been a bit more attentive.
Good service. Portions are nice and big. The roti chicken is a half chicken. Food is delicious and healthy.
Not great :( the lamb kabab did not taste like lamb and the rice was cold. The stars are for the good service.
The food it’s was amazing and 100% Greek original taste . We tried Trio (tzatziki, tarama, tirokauteri) Authentic gyro & Greek salad For desert “homemade milopita”
Friendly place, great food and amazing service. (The octopus is just perfect)
The food is on point Greek and the service efficient and sincere. You’ll love it!
Amazing food! Great decor and atmosphere.

Just came back from a wonderful lunch at this new addition to the neighborhood. Had the hummus and Tzatziki appetizer, salmon sliders and rice and beans. The food and service were wonderful--the coffee is awesome too. Will be returning! efcharistó!

I had high hopes since I’ve been waiting for a new restaurant to open in the neighborhood. This was disappointing at best. The eggs dish had absolutely no flavor to it and the burger was basic. The prices are too high given the quality of the food. That said, the decorations are great. I’d come here for a drink but definitely spend your money elsewhere for brunch.
Delicious food, great wine selection and lovely staff. A wonderful addition to the neighborhood

Amazing space and amazing food! I ordered the seafood pasta and it tasted amazing. Mediterranean desserts were great. Great display of the food as well. Gregorious and Cesar were very helpful.  100% recommend.
Fabulous food...
